---
title: Sloppy Pork Joes served with Creamy Lime Slaw
description: One of the most underrated childhood comfort foods, in our opinion? The humble sloppy Joe. Adults and kids alike will love this version, which has a few flavor upgrades to take it to the next level. Ground pork is browned with scallions, spicy chipotle powder, and a sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning blend, then simmered with pineapple, ketchup, and lime juice until thick and caramelized. The filling’s then stuffed into potato buns with a cabbage and lime slaw for creaminess and crunch. Tasty nostalgia on the table in just 15 minutes? It doesn’t get much better than that.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sloppy-pork-joes-d17f59e5.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sloppy-pork-joes-5fea5bc5e6d08d142e3bbe88-41f4db70.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 42 g
  saturated fat: 13 g
  carbohydrates: 77 g
  sugar: 25 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 970 mg
cuisine: North America
time required: 15 minutes
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sloppy-pork-joes-5fea5bc5e6d08d142e3bbe88
course: main course
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Wash and dry all produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%units}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lime{1%unit}. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce} over a #small bowl{}, reserving juice.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned, ~{3-5%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in step 5).

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, thoroughly combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, scallion greens, @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, lime zest, 1 TBSP reserved pineapple juice (2 TBSP for 4 servings), and a big squeeze of lime juice. Season generously with @salt{generously} and @pepper{to taste}.

Halve @potato buns{2%units}; toast if desired.

Add scallion whites, @sweet and smoky BBQ seasoning{1%tablespoon}, and @chipotle powder{1/4%teaspoon} (add more if you like things spicy) to pan with pork. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add pineapple, @ketchup{4%tablespoon}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} (all for 4 servings), remaining reserved pineapple juice, 1/3 cup @water{1/3%cup} , and a big squeeze of lime juice to pan with pork mixture. Simmer, stirring, until mixture has thickened and pork is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide pork filling and some slaw between buns. Divide sloppy joes between plates. Serve with any remaining slaw and lime wedges on the side.